<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A teenager has been arrested for attempted murder after a young mother out walking with her five-year-old son was allegedly stabbed in a 'vicious and unprovoked attack'. </p>

<p>The victim, 24, was stabbed as she was walking with her five-year-old son in Rudheath Avenue in Withington, Greater Manchester, at around 1.30pm on Saturday. </p>

<p>Police later arrested a 17-year-old boy who is currently being questioned in custody.</p>

<p>The woman was taken to hospital with stab wounds in her leg and is in a stable condition. Her son had no visible injuries. </p>

<p>Detective Inspector John Robb said: 'This was a vicious attack in which a woman was stabbed in front of her young son. Our thoughts are with her and her family as she recovers from this shocking ordeal.</p>

<p>'I would like to reassure the public that this is believed to be an isolated incident and we are not currently looking for anyone else in relation to this attempted murder.'</p>

<p>Anyone with any information is asked to contact police on 0161 856 1420, quoting incident number 1611 of 29/08/2020, or contact Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555111.</p>

<p>The woman was taken to hospital with stab wounds and is in a stable condition. Her son was assessed at the scene by emergency services but had no visible injuries</p>
